articles.author: Robert Lea
articles.title: The chemical contamination of the International Space Station is out of this world (and not in a good way) - Space.com
articles.description: ISS dust appears to hold higher levels of harmful chemicals than floor dust in the United States and Western Europe.
articles.content:
Concentrations of potentially harmful chemical contaminants on the International Space Station (ISS) could exceed those found in dust on floors in homes across the United States and Western Europe.
